SIMPLE: shoveler
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shoveler
<hw>Shov"el*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Also
<ets>shoveller</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who, or that which,
shovels.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A river duck (<spn>Spatula
clypeata</spn>), native of Europe and America. It has a large bill,
broadest towards the tip. The male is handsomely variegated with green,
blue, brown, black, and white on the body; the head and neck are dark
green. Called also <altname>broadbill</altname>,
<altname>spoonbill</altname>, <altname>shovelbill</altname>, and
<altname>maiden duck</altname>. The Australian shoveler, or shovel-nosed
duck (<spn>Spatula rhynchotis</spn>), is a similar species.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shovelful</ent>⟦br⟧
